OL,3,GWales
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FTuesday will start mostly dry
OL,6,Fwith bright spells, especially in the
OL,7,Feast. However, patchy rain will affect
OL,8,Fwest Wales and as the day progresses
OL,9,Flocally heavy showers will break out,
OL,10,Freaching eastern parts by the
OL,11,Fafternoon. Pleasantly warm.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FEarly showers will die out
OL,14,Fduring the evening to leave a largely
OL,15,Fdry night. Some clear intervals,
OL,16,Falthough low cloud, and some mist and
OL,17,Ffog patches are likely to form.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
